Date: Wed, 8 Feb 2017 14:55:59 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1765/2066] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-xs: Add HSCIF1 device
 support

This patch adds the pin control for HSCIF1, and supports connection with
the Debug Serial-1 (CN26) for Salvator-X 2nd version board on R8A7795
ES2.0 SoC.

SCIF1 and HSCI1 are sharing the pin connected to the Debug Serial-1
(CN26) on Salvator-X board, and it is necessary to use it by exclusion.

As for the default of this DeviceTree, SCIF1 is connected.

Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 .../arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts |   14 +++++++++++++-
 1 files changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
index 68d1ff7..b2a81f0 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
@@ -108,6 +108,11 @@
 		function = "scif2";
 	};
 
+	hscif1_pins: hscif1 {
+		groups = "hscif1_data_a", "hscif1_ctrl_a";
+		function = "hscif1";
+	};
+
 	avb_pins: avb {
 		groups = "avb_mdc";
 		function = "avb";
@@ -137,7 +142,7 @@
 &scif1 {
 	pinctrl-0 = <&scif1_pins>;
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
-
+	/* Please use exclusively to the hscif1 node */
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
@@ -148,6 +153,13 @@
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
+&hscif1 {
+	pinctrl-0 = <&hscif1_pins>;
+	pinctrl-names = "default";
+	/* Please use exclusively to the scif1 node */
+	/* status = "okay"; */
+};
+
 &avb {
 	pinctrl-0 = <&avb_pins>;
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
